GJdysJzSgV32Og_BmRZGctKVY-1b5V_0D8kNglk] the results.
Here=E2=80=99s how it works:=C2=A0
Supersapiens ships two sensors to customers, either one-time or on a monthl=
y subscription. Each sensor is the size of a quarter, can be applied in sec=
onds, and lasts 14 days. A monthly subscription costs $140 per month, certa=
inly not cheap, but less than half the cost of Levels=E2=80=99 one-month pl=
an.=C2=A0
The application involves a little skin prick, but 91.6% of people in a surv=
ey said that it was painless.=C2=A0
Once the sensor has been applied, it sends real-time data to the Supersapie=
ns app. Supersapiens is the only external partner with access to Abbott=E2=
=80=99s SaaS product, so it has the most reliable and seamless data on the =
market. The app provides live glucose levels, insights, and snapshots that =
let users understand the impact of food and exercise on their bodies.=C2=A0
The company is also developing a Coaches App that allows coaches to view th=
eir players=E2=80=99 stats all in one place, and Supersapiens is rolling ou=
t the Reader, a Bluetooth-synced wristband that can be worn during competit=
ion to provide easy visibility into glucose levels.=C2=A0
Combined, Supersapiens is building the Energy Management Ecosystem.=C2=A0
Supersapiens has the market-leading CGM for non-diabetic athletes, but it=
=E2=80=99s going to be an increasingly competitive space. That=E2=80=99s wh=
y the Abbott partnership is so key.=C2=A0
