nto biohacking than I was, so I&#8217;d have to make do without it. CGM was=
 clearly important, but so far out of reach.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1=
a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Each person&=
#8217;s body, optimal glucose levels, and responses to different foods are =
unique. By letting people track their glucose levels and adjust in real-tim=
e, CGM has immense benefits:&nbsp;</p><ul style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li styl=
e=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong=
>Energy Management.</strong> Our metabolism produces energy from the food w=
e eat. For our metabolisms to work optimally, we need to keep glucose in a =
healthy and stable range, which we can&#8217;t do accurately without CGM.&n=
bsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format=
: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0;"><strong>Sustain Peak Performance.</strong> Glucose spikes and c=
rashes can lead to fatigue, lethargy, lack of focus, and lack of energy. By=
 monitoring how what you eat and when you eat it impacts your glucose level=
s, you can avoid spikes and crashes.&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.7=
5px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>Stave Off Diabete=
s.</strong> Almost 100 million Americans are pre-diabetic, and most don&#82=
17;t know it. Understanding and adjusting early can help hold off diabetes.=
&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-form=
